      "writtenOn": "2026-04-14T08:41:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "They are stored in different vectors, but the selection happens earlier based on the callback signature.\n\n`REGISTER_EXTENSION_FUNCTION(pelEntryRestored)` currently registers this as an ExtensionLogAssociation: `std::function\u003cvoid(uint32_t, const std::string\u0026)\u003e`\n\nIf I remove `objectPath`, the callback becomes `std::function\u003cvoid(uint32_t)\u003e`, which matches `DeleteFunction` instead.\n\nThat also creates a constructor overload conflict, since Extensions has constructors for both callback types.\n\nSo the second parameter is still needed to keep this registered under the correct extension hook.",
      "parentUuid": "9698ecf5_3bafeb14",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 84,
